			Le Cinque
			=========

A game for learning beginner Italian vocabulary, five words at a
time.  Play it at https://le-cinque.pages.dev -- buono studio!

CURRICULUM

  Five Italian words are laid out with their English translations
  hidden.  Fill in the letters to reveal all five before you run out
  of mistakes.  Over 1,500 everyday words, with spaced repetition so
  the ones you miss come back later.

WORD PRIORITIZATION

  Each round deals five words.  nextWords (api/handlers/game.go) fills
  those five slots by trying four tiers in order, taking words from a
  tier until the round is full or the tier runs dry:

    1. Review (spaced repetition).  Words you lost at least ReviewGap
       (3) finished rounds ago and have not won since; oldest miss
       first, so overdue words return before newer ones.

    2. New words.  Words you have never played, taken in words.tsv
       order.  The curriculum is ordered most-essential first, so
       beginners meet the core vocabulary soonest instead of a random
       scatter across all 1,500+ words.

    3. Not-yet-won, oldest first.  Words you have played but not won
       whose losses are not yet due for review; the ones you saw
       longest ago come first.

    4. Recycle.  Once you have won everything, replay the words you
       won longest ago.

  A typical round mixes a couple of due review words with fresh core
  vocabulary, and only falls back to tiers 3-4 once you have seen most
  of the curriculum.
